I was elected by the software engineering / computer science cohort to act as their representative. This requires me to liaise between the student body and the course lecturers. I conduct meetings with faculty members to help improve the educational system of the school of computer science. I also work on improving the social aspect of student’s life on campus through encouraging active social and educational involvements in university clubs. I was re-elected this year.

In my first year, I was elected to be the first year engineering representative. I represented 800 students and helped with their choice of future engineering studies. I also helped first year engineering students integrate within the wider engineering faculty.

I am actively involved in the charity Uni Camp for Kids as a Leader. The charity is for disadvantaged children to spend time with a large group of university students where they will be taken to pools, ovals and camps to play many different games. I volunteer at four picnics and 1 camp each year. I also volunteer yearly at the city to surf and take part in the charity’s annual tin rattle.
